  "prompt": "Will I get disability benefits for govt jobs after a bike accident?",
  "response": "To get disability benefits for a government job after a bike accident, several factors are considered:\n\n1. Type of Disability:\n- Temporary or permanent disability\n- Severity of the injury\n- Impact on work capacity\n\n2. Employment Status:\n- Whether you were on duty or off-duty during the accident\n- Your current job role and physical requirements\n\n3. Government Disability Policies:\n- Federal or state government job\n- Specific agency's disability guidelines\n- Workers' compensation rules\n- Social Security Disability Insurance (SSDI)\n\n4. Documentation Requirements:\n- Medical records\n- Doctor's assessment\n- Detailed accident report\n- Proof of inability to work\n\n5. Application Process:\n- File claim with employer\n- Submit necessary documents\n- Undergo medical evaluation\n- Wait for approval\n\nRecommended steps:\n- Consult your HR department\n- Get complete medical documentation\n- Seek legal advice if needed\n- Understand your specific agency's disability policies\n\nSpecific details and eligibility depend on your exact situation, job type, and injury severity. Consulting your HR department or a disability benefits expert would provide the most accurate guidance.",
